TY  - JOUR
AU  - Ho, Teng-Suan
AU  - Stapleton, Richard C.
AU  - Subrahmanyam, Marti G.
T1  - Multivariate Binomial Approximations for Asset Prices with Nonstationary Variance and Covariance Characteristics
PY  - 1995
Y1  - 1995/10/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/8.4.1125
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 8
IS  - 4
SP  - 1125
EP  - 1152
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - In this article, we suggest an efficient method of approximating a general, multivariate log-normal distribution by a multivariate binomial process. There are two important features of such multivariate distributions. First, the state variables may have volatilities that change over time. Second, the two or more relevant state variables involved may covary with each other in a specified manner, with a time-varying covariance structure. We discuss the asymptotic properties of the resulting processes and show how the methodology can be used to value a complex, multiple exerciseable option whose payoff depends on the prices of two assets.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/8.4.1125
ER  - 



